com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iprocess.amxbpm.conversion

Class AbstractIProcessToBPMLifeCycleListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iprocess.amxbpm.conversion.AbstractIProcessToBPMLifeCycleListener

  • public abstract class AbstractIProcessToBPMLifeCycleListener
extends Object
    Contributors can contribute a life-cycle listener to the com.tibco.xpd.customer.api.iProcessBpmConversion extension point.

    During a conversion of TIBCO iProcess Modeler XPDL to TIBCO Business Studio XPDL for Active Matrix BPM, life-cycle listeners will be invoked at various significant milestones with in each conversion. The contributor should sub-class this class and override any of the following methods to be notified of the life-cycle events indicated...

  • When Initial import and migration to Business Studio XPDL for iProcess destination is completed (#importAndMigrationComplete(Collection)).
  • When separation of all processes into separate (in memory) process packages (including removal of incoming duplicates) is complete ( #packageSeparationComplete(Collection)).
  • When conversion to XPDL for BPM destination environment is complete (i.e. all conversion extensions performed) ( #conversionExtensionsComplete(Collection, Collection))
  • When conversion is complete and final XPDL file set has been committed to the work space ( #conversionComplete(Collection, Collection, Collection)).


    • One instance of each life-cycle listener contribution is created per-conversion use case (i.e. for each batch of XPDLs selected for import/conversion by the user). Therefore it is possible to persist information gathered through the various life-cycle milestones.


    Additionally, this is also true of each conversion extension. Therefore it should be possible for an individual 3rd party contributor to persist information discovered during each conversion extension and the (for instance) make use of that information once the conversionExtensionsComplete method is invoked, by iterating the given set of executed extensions looking for instances the known 3rd party contributions. For example, the 3rd party contributor may wish to preserve information about XPDL process constructs that may need further user attention after import is complete and then produce a report on these at the end of conversion.


    Each method in the life-cycle is called exactly once when a full conversion is executed without interruption by the user or other fatal error that cause conversion to finish unexpectedly.


Since:
TIBCO Business Studio BPM Edition v3.8

        public abstract org.eclipse.core.runtime.IStatus conversionComplete(Collection<org.eclipse.core.resources.IFile> finalFileSet,
                                                  Collection<com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.Package> studioBPMPackages,
                                                  Collection<com.tibco.xpd.xpdl2.Package> ignoredDuplicatePackages,
                                                  org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
        Invoked when the conversion is complete and the final XPDL file set has been committed to the workspace (including ignoring of incoming XPDL for which processes already exist in the workspace)
        Parameters:
        finalFileSet - The final file set. The set of converted processes for the BPM destination environments.
        studioBPMPackages - The set of process packages (each containing a single process/process interface configured as if for the BPM destination environment).
        ignoredDuplicatePackages - The set of the final processes that were ignored because there is an existing BPM destination process in the workspace with the same name.
        monitor - Standard Eclipse monitor for progress status updates (see IProgressMonitor for more information. This method should call at least monitor.beginTask() at the start of the method and monitor.done() at the end. To overwrite the current progress status message completely, please use only monitor.subTask(string).
        Returns:
        IStatus.OK is the nominal return, Istatus.INFO / WARNING can be used to return information messages (that will be logged with debug mode switched on). IStatus.ERROR status will stop the conversion process and report the error.Use ImportDisplayStatus status type for messages to be displayed to the user at the end of the complete conversion of the XPDL.For more details see ImportDisplayStatus
